Jean Muir (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Muir_(actress) 0 Jean Muir (February 13, 1911 – July 23, 1996) was an American stage and film actress and educator. She was the first performer to be blacklisted after her name appeared in the infamous anti-Communist 1950 pamphlet Red Channels.
